---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How This Works"
  description="The methodology behind Morristown Eats. Visit-first, no pay-to-play, independent coverage only."
>
  <style>
    .v2-header {
      padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
      max-width: 700px;
    }
    .v2-header h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
      line-height: 1.05;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem;
    }
    .v2-header .opener {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      max-width: 560px;
    }
    .v2-body {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0;
      padding-bottom: 6rem;
    }
    .v2-block {
      padding: 3rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-paper-dark);
      max-width: 660px;
    }
    .v2-block:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .v2-block h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      color: var(--color-rust);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .v2-block p {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }
    .v2-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .v2-block .big-statement {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.7rem;
      line-height: 1.3;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .dimensions {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1px;
      margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
      border: 2px solid var(--color-ink);
      box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--color-ink);
    }
    .dimension-cell {
      padding: 1.25rem;
      background: var(--color-paper);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-paper-dark);
    }
    .dimension-name {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--color-rust);
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }
    .dimension-desc {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    }
    .tiers-row {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0;
    }
    .tier-item {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
      padding: 0.9rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--color-paper-dark);
      align-items: start;
    }
    .tier-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .tier-badge {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-ink);
      padding: 3px 7px;
      display: inline-block;
      line-height: 1.4;
      background: var(--color-paper-dark);
    }
    .tier-desc {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--color-ink);
    }
    .tier-desc em {
      font-style: normal;
      color: var(--color-ink-muted);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }
    .rule-stamp {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      color: var(--color-paper);
      background: var(--color-ink);
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--color-rust);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .v2-sig {
      padding: 3rem 0 0;
      border-top: 3px solid var(--color-ink);
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .v2-sig p {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: var(--color-ink-muted);
      max-width: 480px;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-style: italic;
    }
    .v2-sig .sig-name {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--color-rust);
      font-style: normal;
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .v2-header { padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem; }
      .dimensions { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .tier-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.5rem; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="v2-header">
      <span class="label">Methodology</span>
      <h1>How this works</h1>
      <p class="opener">
        Morristown has a better food scene than people give it credit for.
        The problem isn't the restaurants — it's the coverage.
        This is an attempt to fix that.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="v2-body">

      <div class="v2-block">
        <h2>The method</h2>
        <p class="big-statement">Visit first. Pay your own check. Write what you actually think.</p>
        <p>
          Every restaurant in this guide has been personally visited before anything gets
          published. I go as a regular customer, without announcing myself. I order from
          the menu. I pay the bill.
        </p>
        <p>
          Restaurants I've confirmed are open but haven't eaten at yet appear in the
          database clearly marked as unvisited — basic facts only, no editorial take.
          The profile comes after the visit.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="v2-block">
        <h2>What I'm evaluating</h2>
        <p>
          I'm not scoring restaurants against a standard. I'm asking whether a place
          is good at what it's specifically trying to do — and whether that thing
          is worth your time.
        </p>
        <p>
          When I write a profile, I'm thinking about four things:
        </p>
        <div class="dimensions">
          <div class="dimension-cell">
            <span class="dimension-name">Consistency</span>
            <span class="dimension-desc">Is this place reliable across visits, or does it depend on who's working that night?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="dimension-cell">
            <span class="dimension-name">Distinctiveness</span>
            <span class="dimension-desc">Is there something specific here I can't get somewhere else in town?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="dimension-cell">
            <span class="dimension-name">Execution</span>
            <span class="dimension-desc">Does the kitchen deliver on what the menu promises?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="dimension-cell">
            <span class="dimension-name">Local Relevance</span>
            <span class="dimension-desc">Does this place actually serve the community around it?</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
          I don't publish star ratings. Numbers flatten context. A 4.2 doesn't tell you
          whether to order the dumplings. A specific recommendation does.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="v2-block">
        <h2>Who's in the guide</h2>
        <p>
          Independent restaurants in Morristown. Ownership matters to this guide —
          here's exactly how it works:
        </p>
        <div class="tiers-row">
          <div class="tier-item">
            <span class="tier-badge">Independent</span>
            <span class="tier-desc">Privately owned, no institutional ownership or PE backing. <em>Full editorial coverage.</em></span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-item">
            <span class="tier-badge">Local group</span>
            <span class="tier-desc">NJ-focused ownership, 3 or fewer locations. <em>Full coverage, labeled clearly.</em></span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-item">
            <span class="tier-badge">Regional</span>
            <span class="tier-desc">Broader footprint but still genuinely good. <em>Awards categories only.</em></span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-item">
            <span class="tier-badge">National chain</span>
            <span class="tier-desc">Corporate ownership, wide footprint. <em>Not covered.</em></span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">
          When ownership is ambiguous, I research it and disclose what I found.
          The tier is listed on every profile.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="v2-block">
        <h2>The one rule</h2>
        <div class="rule-stamp">No pay-to-play.</div>
        <p>
          Nothing is paid for. Not placement, not profiles, not the order things appear in,
          not the timing of when something gets written. This project exists specifically
          because the alternative — a local food guide with advertising and sponsored
          content — doesn't tell you anything useful.
        </p>
        <p>
          This isn't unusual in principle. It's just not how most local food coverage
          actually operates.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="v2-sig">
      <p>
        I live in Morristown with my family. We eat out constantly —
        probably more than is reasonable. I built this because nothing
        that existed was good enough.
      </p>
      <span class="sig-name">— Matthew</span>
    </div>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>
